          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "divya suseelan"
          },
          "datePublished": "2023-03-15",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "5",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Would like to extend my heartfelt thanks to the management for putting together an amazing event - G Fest. It's not often that you come across a school carnival that is so enjoyable for both kids and parents. The atmosphere was lively and festive, and there was never a dull moment.\nThank you GCIS for a fantastic experience!",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "Green Field International School - Madhavaram"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "vishnu vijay"
          },
          "datePublished": "2023-03-13",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "5",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "One of North Chennai's top CBSE schools, and a genuinely wonderful place to send your kids. They have excellent faculty and an extremely solid infrastructure. Being based in Dubai, I was looking for a school that offered sporting facilities similar to those I have seen in the Emirates. I was looking for a school that offered sports activities along with academics and was pleasantly surprised to find that the school offered Lawn Tennis and basketball.\nThis school is not just about academics, they have offer extracurricular activities as well.\nI would advocate this school to all parents.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "Green Field International School - Madhavaram"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "james palatty"
          },
          "datePublished": "2023-02-22",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "5",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "James Palatty Joseph\nParent of\nCharles James Palatty - 3B\n\nGCIS is a right and great choice for our child, especially this year after noticing the learning gaps of the past two years of online classes. Our child is everyday excited to go to school to be a part of the various academic and extracurricular activities regularly taking place. He is also constructively pursuing his creativity and talents through participating in these activities. The After School Activity programs have given him extra devoted time to further nurture his talents. The school management and faculty have ensured a safe environment as promised which proved to be true as we couldn't see any cultural shock in our child as he quickly got adapted. We are happy that our child is getting adequate opportunities to perform in front of the audience leaving behind his stage fear. Surely, this has also contributed positively to his personality development. We extend our sincere gratitude to the teachers who are taking tremendous efforts to enhance his academic performance too bridging up all types of learning gaps. As our child is spending meaningful time at school, the load upon us the working parents is comparatively less. All in all, he is a happy child at home and school and thanks to the school authority for all the support.\n\nJames P.J.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        }
      ]
